content.text: A document in MongoDB is the same as a record in SQL databases.
content.html: A document in MongoDB is the same as a record in SQL databases.

content.text: To insert a record, or document as it is called in MongoDB, into a collection, we use the insert_one() method.
content.html: To insert a record, or document as it is called in MongoDB, into a collection, we use the insert_one() method.

content.text: The first parameter of the insert_one() method is a dictionary containing the name(s) and value(s) of each field in the document you want to insert.
content.html: The first parameter of the insert_one() method is a dictionary containing the name(s) and value(s) of each field in the document you want to insert.

content.code_html:
import pymongo

myclient = pymongo.MongoClient("mongodb://localhost:27017/")
mydb = myclient["mydatabase"]
mycol = mydb["customers"]

mydict = { "name": "John", "address": "Highway 37" }

x = mycol.insert_one(mydict)

content.text: The insert_one() method returns a InsertOneResult object, which has a property, inserted_id , that holds the id of the inserted document.
content.html: The insert_one() method returns a InsertOneResult object, which has a property, inserted_id, that holds the id of the inserted document.

content.code_html:
mydict = { "name": "Peter", "address": "Lowstreet 27" }

x = mycol.insert_one(mydict)

print(x.inserted_id)

content.text: If you do not specify an _id field, then MongoDB will add one for you and assign a unique id for each document.
content.html: If you do not specify an _id field, then MongoDB will add one for you and assign a unique id for each document.

content.text: In the example above no _id field was specified, so MongoDB assigned a unique _id for the record (document).
content.html: In the example above no _id field was specified, so MongoDB assigned a unique _id for the record (document).

content.text: To insert multiple documents into a collection in MongoDB, we use the insert_many() method.
content.html: To insert multiple documents into a collection in MongoDB, we use the insert_many() method.

content.text: The first parameter of the insert_many() method is a list containing dictionaries with the data you want to insert:
content.html: The first parameter of the insert_many() method is a list containing dictionaries with the data you want to insert:

content.html: The insert_many() method returns a InsertManyResult object, which has a property, inserted_ids, that holds the ids of the inserted documents.

content.text: Insert Multiple Documents, with Specified IDs
If you do not want MongoDB to assign unique ids for your document, you can specify the _id field when you insert the document(s).
content.html: If you do not want MongoDB to assign unique ids for your document, you can specify the _id field when you insert the document(s).

content.text: Remember that the values has to be unique. Two documents cannot have the same _id.
content.html: Remember that the values has to be unique. Two documents cannot have the same _id.
